<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by New York Times News Service clients) 
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The following Arizona Republic story has been added for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Wednesday, Dec. 1. If you
have any questions, please contact the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
GRAVES-MISSING (Juarez, Mexico) _ As U.S. and Mexican officials
began to unearth corpses here Tuesday, they also were exhuming a
cold fear buried along the drug-bloodied border. For more than a
decade, people have simply disappeared in this city of 1.5 million
people, suspected casualties of narco violence and the powerful
Carrillo Fuentes cartel. Jose Alonso Aguilar, 33, was one who
vanished. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
