   BUSH-ECON (Washington) _ Gov. George W. Bush will lay out the
centerpiece of his economic agenda on Wednesday, calling for
sweeping cuts in income tax rates, a tax break for many married
couples and an increase in the child credit, his aides said on
Tuesday. By Richard W. Stevenson.
</P>
