   JORDAN-CAREER (Undated) _ Vernon E. Jordan Jr., a close friend
of President Clinton and a leading political power broker in
Washington, is giving up his senior executive position with the law
firm Akin, Gump, Strauss, Hauer &AMP; Feld to become a partner in
Lazard Freres &AMP; Co., the private investment bank, in New York in
January. Exclusive. By Patrick McGeehan.
</P>
<P>
   BOEING-AIRBUS (Denver) _ Boeing, a proud company that has
dominated commercial aviation since the 1950s, is losing a lot
these days. So far this year, Boeing's big rival, Airbus, has
outsold it by more than 2-1. The lopsided orders have prompted many
in the aviation industry and on Wall Street to think what would
have been unthinkable a decade ago: that Boeing might be in danger
of slipping behind Airbus. By Laurence Zuckerman.
