u v BC-IMPLANT-CORRECTIVE-HN Dec.1 1999 12-01 0116
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-IMPLANT-CORRECTIVE-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   Wednesday, Dec. 1, 1999 Editors  
   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Those newspapers using a story slugged DOW-CORNING-BANKRUPTCY,
datelined Bay City, Mich., that was filed by Hearst Newspapers
yesterday (Tuesday), may want to use the following corrective:
</P>
<P>
   A story, datelined Bay City, Mich., about a federal judge's
approval Tuesday of a plan to allow Dow Corning Corp. to settle
thousands of lawsuits involving the firm's silicone breast implants
contained an incorrect figure. The correct figure is $400 million
for the amount that Dow Corning agreed to set aside for any cases
it might lose from women who do not accept payouts from its overall
$3.2 billion settlement.
</P>
</TEXT>
