r v BC-PAGEEXPRESS-BUDGET-UP     12-01 0195
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-PAGEEXPRESS-BUDGET-UPDATE-NYTSF </SLUG>
 
 PageExpress budget for the week of Nov. 29., 1999
<TEXT>
<P>
   The subject of this week's Focus page has changed. Here is the
new budget line. The page will be available Friday by 2 p.m.
 &UR; FOCUS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BORDER PATROL: The largest buildup in the Border Patrol's
history has sent an army of agents and millions of dollars in
sophisticated equipment to the southwest border to control illegal
immigration. But five years later, the strategy is failing.
Doubling the number of agents has helped the Border Patrol gain
control in places like San Diego and El Paso, but overall
apprehensions of illegal immigrants has reached an all-time high as
the immigrants have simply gone around the Border Patrol blockades.
An amazing 98 percent of those caught are sent back over the border
without any form of punishment, free to try their luck again. Those
who try to go around the blockades are increasingly dying from the
heat and cold, often after people smugglers, who are thriving,
leave stragglers behind during long marches through harsh terrain.
The critical question now is: Should America continue its
billion-dollar buildup?
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-01-99 1214EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
